-- TPG Capital Buys Chinese Packaging Company From Founding Family
-- B y   C a t h y   C h a n
-- 2012-07-26T06:45:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-26/tpg-capital-buys-chinese-packaging-company-from-founding-family.html
TPG Capital, the buyout firm run by
 David Bonderman , bought Chinese packaging company HCP Holdings
Inc. from the founding Chen family, according to a HCP statement
on its website today.  The deal values HCP at about $500 million including debt,
said a person with knowledge of the matter who asked not to be
identified. HCP didnâ€™t disclose the deal value in its statement.  TPG appointed Eddy Wu as chief executive officer of HCP to
replace Jeff Chen, according to the release. Chen will remain
with the company as an  executive director  while Joanne Chen will
continue to serve as chief operating officer, HCP said.  Jeff Chen and Joanne Chen were in meetings and unavailable
to comment on the deal valuation. HCP, founded in Taiwan in
1960, is headquartered in Shanghai and produces packaging
materials for the cosmetics, skincare and fragrance industries.  Link to statement:  http://tinyurl.com/btbkvz9   To contact the reporter on this story:
